  &quot;Chuck Hinson&quot; &lt;chuck.hinson@...&gt; writes:

  &gt; What I&#39;ve read earlier in this thread leads me to believe that some people
  &gt; believe that the second construction in the example would not be RESTful.
  &gt; By my (likely inappropriate) algebra, it seems to me that the second
  &gt; construction would be RESTful, but I really don&#39;t know and was hoping
  &gt; someone could explain.

  It&#39;s not black and white like that.

  One could say that such an app was &quot;not very RESTfull&quot; because it had
  low cacheability for no particular gain (internal, single machine
  performance?)

  But one resource doesn&#39;t really REST make. So to talk about the
  relative RESTfull-ness of it seems pretty odd to me anyway.

  Plus, it&#39;s not black and white like that /8-&gt;

